results.name: Square array, read by antidiagonals, where T(n,k)=n^^k for n>=0, k>=1.
comment: n^^k is defined the left-associative way: n^^2=n^n, n^^3=(n^n)^n=n^(n^2), n^^4=((n^n)^n)^n=n^(n^3), and in general n^^k=n^(n^(k-1)).
results.author: _Robert Munafo_, Jan 21 2010
